lenders.loan_because:
Effective altruism is so important and meaningful, especially in developped countries!

We know that to consume always more is not the ultimate meaning of life. - Instead we can share more, and in fact we can make a big difference for other people with not so much money. For example, even just $100 (one month salary in a poor country) can create new opportunities for a whole family, whereas for us an extra pair of shoes may not really make us happier.

So it's up to us to be more loving & altruistic! :)
